.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "May 2026" "Simple Shell Project" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell is a minimal UNIX command line interpreter written in C.

It reads commands from standard input, parses them, and executes them using system calls such as fork, execve, and wait.

The shell supports:
- Execution of commands
- PATH resolution
- Built-in commands (exit, env)
- Handling of arguments
- Interactive and non-interactive modes

.SH USAGE

Interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ ./simple_shell
$ ls
$ pwd
$ exit
.fi

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
echo "ls -l" | ./simple_shell
.fi

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS

.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell. No arguments are required.

.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.SH FEATURES

- Executes commands using execve
- Searches PATH for executable files
- Handles command arguments
- Displays prompt in interactive mode
- Handles EOF (Ctrl+D)
- Avoids forking if command is not found

.SH ERROR HANDLING

If a command is not found, the shell prints:

.nf
./simple_shell: command: not found
.fi

The shell returns exit status 127 in this case.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH EXAMPLES

.nf
$ ls
$ /bin/ls -l
$ env
$ exit
.fi

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses the global variable:
.B extern char **environ;

